A picture of a young lady processing palm oil locally in a rural environment has attracted an outrage online.  The picture in question A religious fanatic/Facebook user, Chrisray Awodi shared disturbing photos of the unhealthy method some villages making palm oil in Nigeira. The photo in which a scantily dressed lady was seen removing kernel crumbs from the oil has caused outrage online. Chrisray Wrote; “I saw this picture a while ago and I feel it’s outrightly wrong to produce palm oil this way.Could she at least stay out of the pool to do her thing? Why wash herself in it?The question I asked myself was what if she’s menstruating?Haba!”